<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Supermodel Elle Macpherson has offered a look at her wellness regime and revealed how she transformed her body in just one week at age 44, after she showed off her ageless physique in a string bikini earlier this week.</p>

<p>The 56-year-old mother-of-two revealed that while she used to 'rely on genetics' and apply what she did in her 20s and 30s to her 40s and 50s, she soon found that what she had always done wasn't working as well.</p>

<p>'It gets to a point where what you've done your whole life doesn't work anymore,' Australian model Elle Macpherson told British supermodel Rosie Huntington-Whiteley in a podcast.</p>

<p>Scroll down for video </p>

<p>Supermodel Elle Macpherson (pictured) has offered a look at her wellness regime and revealed how she has tweaked her approach now she is in her fifties</p>

<p>Elle went viral earlier this week after she showed off her ageless physique at age 56 in a string bikini earlier this week (pictured)</p>

<p>'I'd always been interested in wellness... And when I had children, I was watching my body evolve and I wanted to learn more about how to support it through all the different phases of my life.'</p>

<p>Elle's interest in wellness and her quest to help her changing body eventually led her to the Harley Street doctor Dr Simone Laubscher in 2008, who opened her eyes to a number of things.</p>

<p>'The incredible Dr Lauscher introduced me to a plant-based diet and explained the importance of having an alkaline body and dietary approach,' Elle said. </p>

<p>The alkaline diet is based on the idea that replacing acid-forming foods with alkaline foods can improve your health.</p>

<p>The 56-year-old (pictured) said while she used to rely on genetics, she swiftly realised that she was going to need to do things differently to her 20s and 30s</p>

<p>* The alkaline diet is based on the idea that replacing acid-forming foods with alkaline foods can improve your health.</p>

<p>Elle (pictured) now follows the alkaline diet, which is based on the idea that replacing acid-forming foods with alkaline foods can improve your health</p>

<p>* Its premise is that your diet can alter the pH value - the measurement of acidity or alkalinity - of your body. </p>

<ul>
<li><p>Certain food groups are considered more acidic, like meat, poultry, fish, eggs, grains and alcohol.</p></li>
<li><p>Others are considered to be more alkaline like fruit, vegetables, nuts and legumes.</p></li>
</ul>

<p>* Your metabolism - the conversion of food into energy - is sometimes compared to fire. Both involve a chemical reaction that breaks down a solid mass. </p>

<p>* When things burn, an ash residue is left behind. Similarly, the foods you eat leave an 'ash' residue known as metabolic waste. </p>

<p>* This metabolic waste can be alkaline, neutral, or acidic. Proponents of this diet claim that metabolic waste can directly affect your body's acidity. </p>

<p>Source: Healthline  </p>

<p>Its premise is that your diet can alter the pH value - the measurement of acidity or alkalinity - of your body. </p>

<p>For Elle, this means replacing acidic foods and drinks like meat, poultry, fish, eggs, grains and alcohol with fruits, nuts, legumes, and vegetables.</p>

<p>Dr Laubscher also introduced the supermodel to other activities that help to lower overall inflammation in the body, such as upping her sleep and reducing her stress load where possible.</p>

<p>Elle's (pictured) interest in wellness and her quest to help her changing body eventually led her to the Harley Street doctor, Dr Simone Laubscher, who put her on the alkaline diet</p>

<ul>
<li><p>BREAKFAST: Egg omelette, plenty of spinach and avocado.</p></li>
<li><p>LUNCH: Salmon with lemon, olive oil, beetroot salad and pearl barley.</p></li>
